"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515401","Home Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>The LIBOR funding allocated to support emergency services staff and volunteers was allocated to a variety of charities covering all the emergency services. The Police and Fire Service treatment and rehabilitation centres and the Air Ambulance Services Charity are among the charities in receipt of LIBOR funding and they support retired as well as serving personnel. Information is not held centrally on proportions of funding allocated to each emergency service or to retired emergency services workers.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","35408","2016-04-27T15:12:58.447Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515401/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515401/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515401/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-25","Emergency Services: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 25 April 2016 to Question 34792, how the £4 million allocation from LIBOR fines that have been allocated for mental health support is being divided between emergency services; and what proportion of that funding will be allocated to (a) firefighters, (b) police officers and staff and (c) paramedics and ambulance staff.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","35410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515402","Home Office","false","2016-05-04","<p>The figures below show the number of Certificates of Sponsorship (CoS) assigned in support of visa applications for Pharmacists in each of the last three years. A Certificate of Sponsorship (CoS) is required to support all visa applications and a sponsor is required to enter a Standard Occupational Classification (SOC) code on their CoS. There is a SoC code for Pharmacists.</p><p>Assigning a CoS does not guarantee a visa will be issued.</p><p>2013 380</p><p>2014 380</p><p>2015 400</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-05-04T13:58:06.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515402/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515402/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-25","Visas: Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many Tier 2 visas have been issued for pharmacists in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","35389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515403","Home Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>The Blue Light Infoline is available now and offers confidential, independent and practical support, advice and signposting around mental health and wellbeing. The Infoline is for emergency service staff, volunteers and their families and helps keep them or those they care about well for work. The infoline can be contacted on 0300 303 5999, or by email on bluelightinfo@mind.org.uk or by text on 84999</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-04-27T15:13:39.33Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515403/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515403/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515403/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-25","Emergency Services: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 25 April 2016 to Question 34792, when she expects the confidential advice line to become available.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","35409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515404","Home Office","false","2016-04-27","<p>The LIBOR funding allocated to support emergency services staff and volunteers was allocated to a variety of charities covering all the emergency services. The Police and Fire Service treatment and rehabilitation centres and the Air Ambulance Services Charity are among the charities in receipt of LIBOR funding and they support retired as well as serving personnel. Information is not held centrally on proportions of funding allocated to each emergency service or to retired emergency services workers.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","35410","2016-04-27T15:12:58.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515404/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515404/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/515404/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-04-25","Emergency Services: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 25 April 2016 to Question 34792, how much of the £10 million allocated to the emergency services from the LIBOR fines will be available to retired emergency service workers.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","35408"
