"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514706","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-29","<p>Since the naming scheme began we have named 490 employers and received 107 representations from employers asking not to be named. Of these 107 employers 85 were ultimately named.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-29T13:45:33.48Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514706/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514706/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514706/answer","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514706/answer/previousversion/57685","Biography information for Nick Boles","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-21","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to his oral contribution of 18 April 2016, Official Report, column 712, on the national minimum wage, how many of the employers who approached his Department and requested not to be named and shamed for breaking national minimum legislation were named and shamed.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","35040"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514707","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-29","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Since the naming scheme began we have received 107 representations from employers asking not to be named: 1 in 2013, 35 in 2014 and 71 in 2015.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-04-29T13:39:39.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514707/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514707/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514707/answer","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514707/answer/previousversion/57687","Biography information for Nick Boles","26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-21","Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to his oral contribution of 18 April 2016, Official Report, column 712, on the national minimum wage, what correspondence his Department has received from employers asking not to be named and shamed for breach of the legislation in each year since that approach was implemented.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","35041"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514708","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-25","<p>The hon. Member’s question was approved on time, but an administrative error with submitting the answer through the Question and Answer system meant that the reply was not sent. Procedures have been put in place to ensure that this issue does not reoccur.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-04-25T13:45:53.823Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514708/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514708/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/514708/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-04-21","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 20 April 2016 to Question 6502, what the reasons are for the time taken to answer that question.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","35076"
